<br />

<br />
It is vague. Your failure to see that doesn't change that.
<br />

<br />
As has already been pointed out, different people have different needs.
<br />

<br />
If I were still using it, I would go with a +HP aug. But that is because I raid alot, and for me HP are more important than just about everything else.
<br />

<br />
If I weren't a raider, I would probably just slap in one of the dropped stat augs (probably a resist, since I only roll on those and STA augs) and be done with it. Why? In groups I tend to take very little damage except when the group is wiping out - a situation where 40 extra HP isn't going to make a difference. Plus, I tend to not melee so a proc aug would be a waste of points.
<br />

<br />
If I wasn't a raider and I liked to melee, I would consider a proc aug. Maybe.
<br />

<br />
There is no <span style="font-weight: bold">best</span> augment for it. There are merely augments that are better suited to a particular persons situation.<br />_________________<br /><span style="font-size: 16px; line-height: normal"><span style="color: red">Zyphyr Runnersbane</span></span>
