				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Some background info would help.. what kind of guild are you in? Are you in the position to get upgrades quite often to your equipment? Is your equipment pretty much the best you are going to get/buy for awhile? If your in a lower tier/familyish guild and you don't upgrade your equip except once in a blue moon look at your stats firstoff and see what needs to be capped. Int I assume would be, then look at Sta.. after that it's your choice really between dex/str/agility vs raising resists. MR/Fire/Cold are going to be your main resists you want to upgrade first if any of them are low. Only if you feel your stats/resists are fine would I consider putting a proc in it.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=660875" target="_blank" class="postlink">Parsalin D'Ayl</a> - 65 Mage of <a href="http://www.cynosureguild.org" target="_blank" class="postlink">Cynosure</a> / Tunare</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
